<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,290,424]" pageId="12" pageNumber="369">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyrick" authorityName=", Meyrick" authorityYear="1908" box="[275,534,290,316]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Dragmatucha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[275,431,290,316]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="369">Dragmatucha</emphasis>
Meyrick
</taxonomicName>
is another Afrotropical genus of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gozmany" authorityYear="1978" box="[1068,1204,290,316]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Torodorinae">Torodorinae</taxonomicName>
with 13 known species (
<bibRefCitation author="Park, K. - T. &amp; Mey, W. &amp; Koo, J. M. &amp; Agassiz, D. J. L. &amp; Aarvik, L." box="[208,403,326,352]" pageId="12" pageNumber="369" pagination="151 - 175" refId="ref10310" refString="Park, K. - T., Mey, W., Koo, J. M., Agassiz, D. J. L. &amp; Aarvik, L. (2020 b) A taxonomic review of the Afrotropical genus Dragmatucha Meyrick, 1908 (Lepidoptera, Gelechioidea, Lecithoceridae, Torodorinae), with descriptions of eleven new species. Zootaxa, 4786 (2), 151 - 175. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4786.2.1" type="journal article" year="2020">
Park 
<emphasis box="[267,323,326,352]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="369">et al.</emphasis>
2020b
</bibRefCitation>
). Recently 
<bibRefCitation author="Park, K. - T. &amp; Karisch, T." box="[527,780,326,352]" pageId="12" pageNumber="369" pagination="581 - 593" refId="ref10153" refString="Park, K. - T. &amp; Karisch, T. (2021) Lecithoceridae (Lepidoptera, Gelechioidea) of Bioko Island, with description of two new species (Lepidoptera, Gelechioidea, Lecithoceridae). Zootaxa, 4995 (3), 581 - 593. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4995.3.12" type="journal article" year="2021">Park &amp; Karisch (2021)</bibRefCitation>
described additional one species from Bioko Island (
<collectingCountry name="Equatorial Guinea" pageId="12" pageNumber="369">Equatorial Guinea</collectingCountry>
). The genus is characterized by the forewing venation with M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[981,989,380,394]" fontSize="6" pageId="12" pageNumber="369">3</subScript>
coincident with CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1224,1232,380,394]" fontSize="6" pageId="12" pageNumber="369">1</subScript>
, and the hind tibia is roughly tufted with long piliform scales.
</paragraph>
